**Abstract:**
Working notes titled "Assent and Consent" exploring Lonergan's distinction between intellectual assent (act of intellect concerning truth) and consent (act of will concerning the good). Critiques medieval treatment of biblical narratives as objects for intellectual assent, arguing they reduced faith to the order of contemplation rather than exposure and interaction.

